        <mxCell id="mfMDxRqSIfLdnLeMbxml-153" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=top;rounded=0;" value="Text definotion:&amp;nbsp; (Yapping is normal in electrotechnics)&amp;nbsp;&lt;div&gt;The LED stripps will be all wired in paralled with even power injection. For now I see the need for&amp;nbsp; 8 Power injections along the way, but we&#39;ll find out later when we wire all the LED strips in series and then we can worry about power injections.&lt;br&gt;The LED sptrip wiring is interesting, as there will be two strips wired in paralell and they will share the same pixel mapping because of they&#39;re wired in paralel. Then it will go to the two strips below and etc.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;And in the middle we have to have another GPIO from TwinkleTron for the bottom rows as I don&#39;t think the signal would be suitable as this point.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Almost evhery wire is going on the backside, with local connections being on the front side, That&#39;s also true for BCB&#39;s lol.&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="280" width="760" x="34" y="1919" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="mfMDxRqSIfLdnLeMbxml-155" parent="1" style="shape=image;verticalLabelPosition=bottom;labelBackgroundColor=default;verticalAlign=top;aspect=fixed;imageAspect=0;image=data:image/png,;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="640" width="319.59" x="259" y="1279" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
